cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and proposes a neural network architecture and learning algorithm that can be applied to various NLP tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also emphasizes the use of internal representations learned from vast amounts of mostly unlabeled training data, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions named entity recognition, which is a task related to information extraction, and therefore it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) since some NLP tasks, such as semantic role labeling, can be seen as a form of image analysis.
